        • Weather-resistant outdoor camera for year-round security - The wireless camera is certified and tested to withstand the toughest conditions in heat, cold, rain, or sun
        • Simple to set up. Easy to recharge - Maximize the use of your wireless indoor and outdoor security camera and get up to 6 months of battery life on one charge
        • Works seamlessly with your smart home - This home camera works as an Amazon Alexa device, Google device, Apple HomeKit device and Samsung SmartThings device
        • Arlo Secure - Includes 3-months of Arlo Secure for 30-day cloud recording, advanced object detection, rich notifications, cloud activity zones and more. Plans start at dollar 2.99 per month for a single camera, and dollar 9.99 for unlimited cameras.

        Jeremy Johnson
        4.0 out of 5 stars Somewhere between an Arlo Pro 2 and 3 -- plus Wifi
        Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2020
        Color: WhiteSize: 1 CameraStyle: Standard Verified Purchase
        This camera is perfect for what it does. It gives you all the benefits of having an Arlo camera (battery powered, great app, reliable smart alerts, etc) without needing a base station. In my case I have a very large property and have covered much of it with outdoor wireless access points so my WiFi coverage is MUCH larger than my base station coverage. I have three Arlo Pro 2's that cover that area and I have two Arlo Go's (send data over Verizon instead of WiFi) that cover locations outside my base station coverage area. With the Essential camera I can replace the Go's no problem. Bottom line for me is that these are an perfect fit for anyone with a large area and is comfortable setting up access points (I recommend Ubiquiti's line of switches, gateways, and access points).

        The reason I give it 4 stars instead of 5 is because I believe this camera is needlessly hobbled. The first issue is that it has a micro USB port for charging instead of the magnetic charging option on the Arlo Pro 3's. The second issue is that the battery is not removable/replaceable. For some this may be a dealbreaker and it almost is for me. I can only hope they come out with a Essential Pro camera that has direct-to-WiFi, but also the replaceable battery and magnetic charging.

        Joeyb
        1.0 out of 5 stars Tech support issues
        Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2020
        Color: WhiteSize: 3 CamerasStyle: Standard Verified Purchase
        After reading some reviews I decided to purchase this wireless camera system. The initial set up was frustrating to say the least. The first camera would sync but I had issues with the other 2. (3 camera kit) I consider myself to be some what tech savvy but after considerable time I could not get these to work on any of my devices.

        The online support was not helpful. After about a month I returned the system. The worst part of this experience was the tech support. It was a complete fail on all fronts. There seems to be 3 ways to contact Arlo support. (Chat, Help ticket and by phone)

        I'll start first with the chat. I don't know if they were all on lunch break but no one answered me. Second was help ticket. After some time they got back to me through email and recommended that I move closer to the base station when syncing....this system doesn't have one. I wrote back explaining that I had the essential without the base station only to get yet another email stating I should move closer to the base station when syncing. So I decided to call the tech support line. I gave up after 2 hours on hold.

        I still receive emails about my case and other products. I've tried to unsubscribe to them but when I do it tells me my email is not on file......I'm serious.

        So, even if you have purchased or are considering purchasing this product I would think twice.

        I ended up buying an Eufy based on another customers recommendation who had issues with the Arlo system as well. So far it's worked out very well and system was priced less.

        SHAWN M
        3.0 out of 5 stars Mix of good and bad - know what you are getting
        Reviewed in Canada on January 17, 2021
        Color: WhiteSize: 1 CameraStyle: Standard Verified Purchase
        Picture quality is very good and the camera is easy to set up (I connected via an existing base station VMB4000 series using the Arlo app). With the 3 month trial subscription, the functionality is everything I've come to expect from Arlo based on my previous experiences with the Pro2 camera.
        Battery life is extremely dependent on what you are using the camera for. If you are monitoring a high traffic area, you won't get a month out of it - even if you set it for optimized power management. Using it to monitor a more limited area without high traffic (I've been using it to monitor my garage entry) 3 or 4 months seems reasonable. The only way you'll get 6 months is if you point it at a wall so that it never triggers.
        As mentioned, functionality is great - as long as you have a subscription. Once you don't the limitations become overwhelming. I had expected that since I was paired to an existing base station with USB storage attached that I'd be able to review recordings using the app the same way as I do for my other Arlo camera (Pro2). Turns out, that compatibility isn't there. If you want to see the recordings, you need to eject the USB from the base and view the recordings on a computer (not the app). Seems like a real pain (it is) and either a very poor design choice for compatibility, or a blatant attempt to drive people to continue with a paid subscription once the trial expires. There are base station models that will still let you view Arlo Essential recordings on the app from local storage, but it's not worth it to me to upgrade a base station that works just fine for my existing camera.
